'''''Attack Force''''' is a 1980 video game developed by [[Big Five Software]] for the [[TRS-80]] 16K. It was written by Big Five co-founders Bill Hogue and Jeff Konyu.<ref name="giantlist"/> Hogue later wrote ''[[Miner 2049'er]]''. ''Attack Force'' is based on [[Exidy]]'s 1980 [[Targ (video game)|Targ]] arcade game.<ref name="trs80">{{cite web |url=http://www.trs-80.org/attack-force/ |date= |title=Attack Force |last=Reed |first=Mathew |website=TRS-80.org}}</ref><ref name="Linzmayer1981">{{cite magazine |last=Linzmayer |first=Owen |date=September 1981 |title=Bringing Home the Arcade |url=https://archive.org/details/creativecomputing-1981-09/page/n187 |magazine=[[Creative Computing (magazine)|Creative Computing]] |publisher=Creative Computing |location=Morristown, NJ |volume=7 |issue=9 |pages=180â€“183 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Attack Force'' is a game in which the player's ship must avoid the twisting and turning ram-ships of the enemy.<ref name="SG"/><ref name="Kwascha1983">{{cite book |last=Kwascha |first=George |editor-last=Fiderio |editor-first=Janet |year=1983 |title=80 Micro's Review Guide |url=https://archive.org/details/80MicrosReviewGuide |publisher=80 Micro Books |location=Peterborough, NH |chapter=Attack Force |page=[https://archive.org/details/80MicrosReviewGuide/page/n104 90]}}</ref>

==Reception==
J. Mishcon reviewed ''Attack Force'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 39.<ref name="SG">{{cite magazine |last=Mishcon |first=J. |date=May 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=39|pages=35}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "This is another strong entry in the Big Five line and I strongly recommend it for any arcade buff."<ref name="SG"/>

